  (6, 'production', 'B', 'Displays a mature approach to production, handling the final semester''s pressures with steady control and professional conduct — a strong foundation for industry work to keep building on.'),
  (6, 'production', 'B', 'The work is of a high standard. Advice to refine the more intricate, specialized details through a focused finishing review — this precision comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'production', 'B', 'Maintains a consistent, logical production workflow that yields a functional, aesthetically sound result. To progress further, push the finish toward a premium standard — which comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'production', 'B', 'Shows a reliable ability to execute complex ideas and is moving toward a professional standard. Advice to close the remaining gap through targeted polishing passes — this final refinement comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'production', 'C', 'You contribute reliably to the team. Advice to step into a stronger ownership role by taking responsibility for a clear part of the schedule and seeing it through delivery — this leadership grows through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'production', 'C', 'The basic technical requirements are met. Advice to develop proactive contingency strategies by listing likely risks before the shoot and preparing a backup plan for each — this foresight keeps production stable and grows through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'production', 'C', 'The production is functional. Advice to develop consistent control over the project''s many demands by breaking them into a tracked schedule and managing each item to completion — this control comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'production', 'C', 'Successfully aligns the final outcome with the basic objectives. Advice to bring clearer execution to fully realize the vision by checking, at each stage, that the work communicates the intended idea — this clarity develops through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'production', 'C', 'You managed the final production cycle through to completion. Advice to synchronize your middle-stage logistics with your delivery goals by mapping each logistical step back to the final deadline so nothing slips — this coordination strengthens through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'production', 'C', 'Core production tasks are present. Advice to develop the reliable, detailed production flow expected at the conclusion of the course by following a consistent routine and reviewing each stage before moving on — this reliability comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'production', 'C', 'Shows a foundational grasp of final-year theory. Advice to clear the recurring minor errors in execution through a careful review pass before delivery, lifting the work toward professional output — accuracy that comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'production', 'C', 'The work is complete and meets the brief. Advice to develop a more rigorous, precise approach — careful planning and a dedicated finishing pass — to achieve a cohesive, polished result; this comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'production', 'D', 'You are advised to maintain a functional presence on set. The next step is to take clearer ownership of your role by leading a defined part of the production and seeing it through — this responsibility is essential and must be developed. Advised repeated practice and teamwork.'),
  (6, 'production', 'D', 'The final production is short of the required technical standard at present. Please build the practical discipline expected of a graduate by following a rigorous, improve step-by-step routines with checks at each stage — discipline develops through repeated practice and teamwork.'),
  (6, 'production', 'D', 'Your on set disicpline lacks practical efficiency. Please get organised and adopt a more rigorous practical discipline by preparing thoroughly beforehand and following a clear checklist for each setup — this professionalism on set develops through repeated practice and teamwork.'),
  (6, 'production', 'D', 'Maintains a steady work rate on set — a good start but not enough. Advice to tighten the connection between your choices and the shot list by checking each setup before shooting — this coordination strengthens through repeated practice and debrief.'),
  (6, 'production', 'D', 'You need to contribute to the crew reliably. Advice to develop executive-level control over your role by taking clear ownership of your responsibilities and coordinating proactively with other departments — this leadership grows through repeated practice and teamwork.'),
  (6, 'production', 'D', 'You are expected to handle coordination at a professional level. Advice to master professional coordination — better planning, communicaiton, clear schedules, call sheets, and communication between departments. Ensure you provide the stable administrative base a graduation project needs; this comes through repeated practice and teamwork.'),
  (6, 'production', 'D', 'Your scheduling must improve. Advice to incorporate precision logistics by using exact timestamps for each technical setup rather than broad time blocks, so the day runs to plan — this precise scheduling and monitoring is crucial and it strengthens through repeated practice and teamwork.'),
  (6, 'production', 'D', 'Your participation on set needs to be proactive. Advice to develop more proactive participation by anticipating technical needs before they arise — preparing equipment and setups ahead of each shot, actors arrival, food etc — which becomes disciplined and instinctive through repeated practice and teamwork.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Demonstrates strong ability to develops original concepts with confidence, supported by clear research and well-defined narrative intent. Well done.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Shows a clear grasp of story fundamentals — premise, conflict, and character motivation — and applies them effectively. Keep it up.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Writes with clarity and visual awareness, translating ideas into cinematic, engaging scenes. Well done.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Demonstrates strong control over basic story structure, creating coherent narratives using the three-act framework. Keep it up.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Brings originality and depth to creative writing exercises, with a distinct narrative voice and perspective. Good work.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Effectively develops characters with clear motivations that drive meaningful narrative progression. Well done.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Observes keenly, translating real-life experiences into compelling story ideas. Well done.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Actively reads and analyses stories, and applies those insights to their own writing practice — a habit that will keep deepening their craft as the reading widens. Keep it up.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Understands concept development well. Advice to refine each idea to a single clear premise line and pressure-test it for focus — clearer, sharper concepts come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Is familiar with story fundamentals. Advice to anchor every scene in a clear character want and a clear obstacle so conflict and motivation stay consistent — this consistency comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Writes with clear, readable scenes. Advice to develop stronger cinematic detail by describing what we see and hear in concrete, specific images — visual writing sharpens through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Understands the three-act structure. Advice to strengthen the act turns and raise stakes at each so progression feels dynamic and engaging — this comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Shows real effort in creative writing. Advice to push past the first idea and ground writing in specific, lived detail — stronger originality and depth come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Develops characters with some clarity. Advice to build individuality through specific backstory, contradictions, and a personal want — distinctive, layered characters come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Engages with observational exercises. Advice to turn observations into stories by asking what conflict or change each moment could spark — translating observation into ideas strengthens through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Engages with reading tasks. Advice to turn each reading into one concrete technique to try in the next draft — applying insights to your own writing strengthens through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Concept development is becoming clearer. Advice to distil each idea to a single sharp premise line and pressure-test it for focus — clearer concepts come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Has a partial grasp of story fundamentals. Advice to define a clear central conflict — who wants what, against what — and develop it scene by scene, which strengthens through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Visual clarity is developing. Advice to translate ideas into concrete images we can see and hear on screen, scene by scene — cinematic writing sharpens through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Shows a developing grasp of story structure. Advice to outline each story against the three-act framework before drafting, so set-up, conflict and resolution land clearly — structure becomes second nature with repeated practice.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Creative writing exercises are taking shape. Advice to push past the first, predictable idea and ground writing in specific, lived detail — originality and depth come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Characters are starting to take shape. Advice to give each a clear want and a stake in the outcome so their motivations drive the story — well-motivated characters come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Observational exercises show potential. Advice to ask what conflict or change each observed moment could spark, turning notes into scenes — translating observation into story material strengthens through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Is engaging more with reading and analysis. Advice to convert each reading into one concrete technique to try in the next draft — applying insights to your writing strengthens through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Concept development is beginning to form. Advice to work on distiling each idea to a single clear premise line and carry it through to a complete piece. Student is expected to deliver clear, finished concepts, a skill that comes through repeated writing practice.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Is slowly becoming familiar with the basics of premise, conflict, and character. Advice to plan each of these clearly before drafting a scene. A firmer grasp of story elements comes through repeated practice is expected.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Writing is developing toward screenplay form. Advice to write in concrete present-tense action describing only what we see and hear, in standard format — cinematic readability comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Shows an early grasp of basic story structure. Advice to outline each story as set-up, conflict, and resolution before drafting — a sense of structure grows through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Creative writing exercises are getting under way. Advice to carry each idea through to a full, finished piece and develop it with specific detail — completion and depth come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Characters are at an early stage. Advice to define each one''s want, role in the story, and a defining trait so their purpose is clear — well-drawn characters come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Is beginning to engage with observation and ideation. Advice to ask what conflict or change each observed moment could spark and develop the strongest into scenes — turning observation into ideas grows through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (1, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Engagement with reading and analysis is developing. Advice to take part actively and turn each reading into a technique to try in your own writing — application strengthens through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Writes natural, character-driven dialogue that reveals subtext with minimal reliance on exposition.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Demonstrates strong control over scene writing, with clear progression, conflict, and purpose in every scene.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Applies advanced structures such as the Hero''s Journey and Story Circle effectively to build engaging, well-shaped narratives.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Understands conflict well, creating tension that consistently drives the narrative forward.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Writes distinct character voices, making dialogue identifiable and unique to each character — a real strength to keep stretching with more varied roles.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Writes with strong awareness of rhythm and pacing, letting scenes flow naturally and effectively.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Uses dialogue effectively across situations, adapting tone and style to suit context and character.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Integrates writing with visual thinking, ensuring scenes are cinematic and performable.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Writes dialogue that serves the narrative. Advice to let characters speak indirectly and withhold what''s obvious so lines feel less predictable and explanatory — natural, layered dialogue comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Understands the basics of scene construction. Advice to give each scene a clear want, an obstacle, and a turn so progression and conflict strengthen — purposeful scenes come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Applies story structures appropriately. Advice to push each idea past the obvious turn — develop greater depth and originality by drafting two or three alternative versions of key beats, which sharpens through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Shows awareness of conflict. Advice to ensure every scene carries some friction, internal or external, so tension runs throughout — consistent conflict comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Characters show some distinction. Advice to develop stronger individual voices by writing a short solo speech for each character — distinct, identifiable dialogue comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Has basic control over pacing. Advice to even out the rhythm by trimming scenes that linger and giving key beats room to breathe — smooth pacing comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Writes dialogue that suits the situation. Advice to vary tone with the emotional temperature of each scene and each character''s state — tonal range in dialogue comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Understands cinematic writing. Advice to strengthen execution by choosing the most telling image for each beat and writing it in concrete, specific terms — impactful visual writing comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Dialogue is gaining depth. Advice to lean on subtext and give each character their own speech pattern so conversations feel natural and emotionally layered — this develops through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Scene writing is becoming more consistent. Advice to give each scene a clear purpose and a turn that moves the story on — purposeful progression comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Shows a developing grasp of story structures. Advice to outline beats in order and check each leads into the next so the narrative flows — smooth flow comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Conflict is beginning to emerge. Advice to define what each character wants and what blocks them, then keep that friction alive in every scene — clear, consistent conflict comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Character voices are developing. Advice to give each character a distinct vocabulary, rhythm, and way of avoiding the point — distinct, non-repetitive voices come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Pacing is coming under control. Advice to restructure scenes and tighten transitions so the rhythm evens out — smoother, more engaging flow comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Dialogue is starting to fit situation and character intent. Advice to clarify what each character wants from a line before writing it — clearer, purposeful dialogue comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Cinematic quality is emerging. Advice to visualise each scene as concrete action and to write moments actors can play — clearer, more performable scenes come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Dialogue shows emerging clarity. Advice to give every line a purpose and each character a distinct way of speaking — purposeful, distinctive dialogue comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Scene writing is starting to take structure. Advice to give each scene a clear opening, a development through conflict, and a turn or resolution — well-shaped scenes come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Shows an emerging grasp of story structures. Advice to outline beats in order and check each leads logically into the next — strong narrative progression comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Conflict is beginning to emerge. Advice to state plainly what each character wants and what blocks them, then keep that tension running through every scene — clear, consistent conflict comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Characters are at an early stage. Advice to give each a clear motivation and a distinct voice through specific honest choices — voice and motivation strengthen through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Pacing is starting to come under control. Advice to restructure scenes and tighten transitions so the writing flows rather than feeling disjointed — smooth pacing comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Dialogue is starting to fit situation and character. Advice to read lines aloud and ask what each character truly wants from them — credible, clear dialogue comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (2, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Is engaging with the basic screenwriting skills. Advice to practise the fundamentals — premise, conflict, scene structure, and visual writing — build a writing practice to build these skills build steadily.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Commands narrative theory well, applying story vs discourse, character arcs, and archetypes with clarity and precision, while keeping dialogue economical and character-specific so subtext emerges naturally.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Controls structure clearly through frameworks such as the Fichtean Curve and Seven-Point Structure, with visually driven scenes, strong pre-visualisation, and purposeful dialogue.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Integrates theme and premise seamlessly into scene construction, with every beat advancing both story and character, and subtext consistently shaping interactions.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Uses genre conventions with originality and confidence, weaving dialogue, action, and visual elements together into layered storytelling.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Balances character- and plot-driven storytelling with well-defined arcs and purposeful escalation, and uses rhythm, pauses, and interruption in dialogue to enhance emotional beats.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Researches and develops rigorously, producing well-realised settings and coherent worlds, with precise visual writing and clear, cinematic staging.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Constructs strong scenes with clear conflict, progression, and emotional layering, letting subtext emerge effectively through behaviour and interaction.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Overall work integrates narrative theory, structure, genre, and craft at a high level, with consistently controlled, purposeful dialogue, subtext, and visual storytelling.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Understands narrative principles and character arcs well. Advice to apply story vs discourse more consistently by varying how events are revealed, and to cut direct exposition in favour of implication — this develops through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Is familiar with structural frameworks. Advice to outline beats precisely before drafting for cleaner progression, and to sharpen visual writing with specific, concrete images of what we see and hear — both develop through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Overall work is competent and well-structured. Advice to integrate theory, structure, and expressive technique by letting structural choices serve theme and character in each draft — this integration deepens through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Theme and premise are present. Advice to let them shape concrete character decisions in each scene and to sustain subtext throughout rather than in moments — this integration comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Shows awareness of genre conventions. Advice to play with and subvert those conventions for originality, and to let more scenes carry meaning through image rather than dialogue — both develop through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Character arcs are identifiable. Advice to map each character''s want and change across the script for greater depth and consistency, and to give each a distinct vocabulary and rhythm so their voices differentiate clearly.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Scene construction supports narrative progression. Advice to sharpen pacing and escalation by raising stakes each scene, and to convey emotion through behaviour and implication rather than statement — this comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Research and development are evident. Advice to deepen world-building with specific sensory detail and to pre-visualise scenes shot by shot so visual elements work harder — both strengthen through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Has a basic grasp of narrative concepts. Advice to practise varying how events are revealed (discourse) versus what happens (story), and to make dialogue character-specific — both develop through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Is beginning to apply structural frameworks. Advice to outline beats against the framework before drafting for even progression, and to add visual action alongside dialogue — both strengthen through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Theme and premise are starting to emerge. Advice to let them steer concrete story choices and to sustain subtext beyond literal exchanges — clearer thematic direction comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Is building an understanding of genre. Advice to study the tonal and structural conventions of the target genre and apply them consistently for a clear genre identity — this comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Character arcs are developing. Advice to define each character''s start and end point so transformation reads clearly and consistently, and to show emotion through behaviour rather than statement — this comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Scenes are functional. Advice to build each around a want, an obstacle, and a turn, and to stage emotional beats through behaviour — stronger dramatic purpose comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Research and development are at an early stage. Advice to ground settings in specific detail and write scenes as concrete images we can see and hear, not literary description — cinematic expression develops through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Overall work meets the basic requirements. Advice to outline clearly before drafting and revise for consistency across narrative, genre, and craft — stronger structure and clarity come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Is beginning to understand narrative structure. Advice to separate what happens (story) from how it is revealed (presentation), and to let dialogue come from character need rather than explanation — both grow steadily through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Is building the Semester III skills. Advice to focus on constructing scenes with clear conflict, writing character-driven dialogue, and showing story through image — these strengthen together through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Is learning to apply basic structural frameworks. Advice to outline beats in order before drafting and check each scene leads into the next — smooth progression and coherent scenes come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Is beginning to work with theme and premise. Advice to state both clearly and let them shape concrete scene choices, and to build subtext into interactions — this integration comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Is building an understanding of genre. Advice to study the tonal and structural conventions of the chosen genre and apply them consistently — tonal control and impact come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Character development is beginning to form. Advice to give each character a clear want and a change to undergo, and a distinct way of speaking — well-defined, individual characters come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Needs to practice structuring scenes. Advice to build each dramatic choice around a want, an obstacle, and a turn, with clear internal conflict and emotional movement — strong, purposeful scenes come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (3, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Is beginning to research and develop ideas. Advice to gather specific detail and pre-visualise each scene shot by shot, writing it as concrete action — focused research and development and strong visual writing come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Handles storytelling techniques with control, using devices such as the McGuffin and indirect narration to shape layered narratives.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Constructs scenes with precise control of dramatic tension, using pacing, retardation, and subtext to sustain engagement throughout.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Handles complex structures, including non-linear timelines and ellipsis, with impressive clarity and coherence.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Creates effective montage sequences, integrating voice-over, music, and natural sound to carry meaning visually.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Adapts writing effectively across film, television, and web, showing clear command of each format''s structural and tonal differences.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Develops a well-structured web series bible, with strong episodic arcs, character continuity, and clear season-level progression.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Thinks collaboratively, contributing effectively to writers'' room processes and idea development.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Controls dialogue, subtext, and visual writing consistently, with scenes driven by conflict, mood, and cinematic clarity.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Understands storytelling techniques well. Advice to apply devices such as the McGuffin or indirect narration with clear intent about what each adds to the story — consistent, purposeful use comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Shows awareness of dramatic tension and pacing. Advice to escalate stakes scene by scene and vary scene length to control rhythm — confident pacing and escalation come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Uses non-linear elements such as ellipsis and reverse chronology. Advice to make each temporal shift purposeful and clearly signposted so the reader always knows where they are — clarity in non-linear work comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Montage sequences are functional. Advice to decide what each montage must achieve emotionally, then pair image with sound so they amplify rather than merely accompany each other — purposeful montage comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Understands that formats differ. Advice to study the specific structural and tonal conventions of film, television, and web writing and write to each one''s logic — this precision, which strengthens authenticity, comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'The web series bible is structured. Advice to clarify each episode''s arc and chart how the story builds across the season — clear long-term development comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Participates in collaborative development. Advice to build actively on others'' pitches by adding a concrete next beat or complication — a more defined contribution to the room comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Dialogue is functional but sometimes explains too much. Advice to practise saying less in dialogue and showing more through action and image, letting subtext carry the emotion — this restraint develops through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Has a basic grasp of storytelling techniques. Advice to deploy each with clear intent and notice how structure, character, and theme interact — that interplay, which gives a script depth, develops through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Is starting to build dramatic tension. Advice to study how scene length and beat placement build and release tension, then revise to control that rhythm — pacing, the engine of engagement, develops through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Non-linear storytelling is still developing. Advice to make every departure from chronology earn its place by serving the story''s emotional or thematic logic, and to signpost it clearly — coherent non-linear writing comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Is starting to attempt montage. Advice to decide what each montage must achieve emotionally before writing it, then design sound to amplify rather than merely accompany the image — purposeful montage comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Is beginning to write across formats. Advice to study the distinct conventions of film, television, and web writing and apply each one''s structural logic — format fluency comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'The web series bible is in early development. Advice to shape each episode''s flow and give every main character a clear journey across the series — a stronger bible comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Is beginning to take part in collaborative work. Advice to contribute regularly and build on others'' pitches by adding a concrete next beat or twist — a stronger room presence comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (4, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Dialogue is currently direct and explanatory. Advice to practise scenes where characters say less than they mean and the image carries the meaning — subtext and visual storytelling grow stronger through repeated practice and feedback.'),
