  (5, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Writes well-structured synopses with defined arcs, clear stakes, and progression that reflects feature-length storytelling logic.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Shows a critical understanding of how structure shapes meaning, evaluating and employing non-linear and non-dramatic forms thoughtfully in relation to theme and audience.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Selects and develops feature ideas with strong conceptual clarity, showing clear awareness of scalability, sustainability, and adaptation potential.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Understands non-linear and experimental structures well. Advice to signpost each time-shift clearly so the reader always knows where they are — clean transitions in non-linear work come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Shows awareness of adaptation. Advice to transform the source more boldly by re-asking its theme through a new context, character, or point of view — meaningful reinterpretation develops through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Engages with real-life material. Advice to decide whose perspective the story is told from and to weigh how real people are represented — thoughtful ethical framing develops through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Advertisement concepts read clearly. Advice to sharpen the one-liner to a single memorable hook and storyboard the visual beat-by-beat — concise, visually defined ads come through repeated drafting and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Feature-length ideas show promise. Advice to define the central theme and trim the scope to what one feature can hold — focused, scalable ideas come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Synopses are coherently structured. Advice to map each character''s arc and the rising stakes explicitly before drafting so the emotional drive stays even — this planning habit strengthens through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Shows awareness of what feature development demands. Advice to test each idea for enough conflict and subplot to fill a feature, deepening theme and stakes so it sustains long-form — this judgement develops through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Understands structural choices. Advice to align structure with theme and the audience''s emotional journey, choosing each form because it serves the story — this connection develops through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Has a basic grasp of non-linear structures. Advice to clarify each time-shift and keep an underlying through-line so the audience can follow easily — clarity in alternative structures comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Has a basic grasp of non-linear structures. Advice to give each departure from chronology a clear story reason and signpost it so the reader stays oriented — controlled non-linear writing comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Is beginning to engage with real-life events. Advice to research the material closely and decide whose perspective frames the story and how real people are portrayed — depth and ethical sensitivity come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Advertisement writing is still finding its focus. Advice to start from one sharp central idea expressed in a single line before adding visuals — focused, engaging concepts come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Feature-length ideas are forming. Advice to anchor each in one clear premise and a guiding theme so it has direction and cohesion — focused feature ideas come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Synopses are loosely structured at present. Advice to lay out the major plot points in order and link each to the next as cause and effect — clear arcs and progression come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Structural intent is still developing. Advice to choose each structural decision because it serves the theme or emotional journey, not for its own sake — intentional, cohesive form comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Feature concepts are emerging. Advice to test each idea for enough conflict, subplot, and theme to fill a feature, then deepen the premise accordingly — long-form judgement comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Needs stronger understanding of non-linear and experimental structures. Advice to choose each form because it serves the story and keep it clear for the audience — confident experimental writing comes through repeated practice and feedback. Please work on this.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Would benefit form deeper engagement in source material. Advice to interpret the source closely, make deliberate adaptation choices, and recontextualise its theme in a new setting or viewpoint — strong adaptation comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Real-life narratives need clearer framing and stronger consideration of perspective. Advice to choose whose perspective frames the story, set the context clearly, and weigh how real people are represented — thoughtful real-life storytelling comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Feature-length ideas need further development. Advice to anchor each in a clear premise, define what is at stake, and chart its direction — stronger long-form potential comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Advertisement concepts would benefit from a more clearly defined central idea, target audience, and communicative intent. Advice to practice this - by naming the single central idea, the target audience, and what it must communicate before writing — focused ad concepts come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Synopses are beginning to form. Advice to order the major beats clearly and track each character''s movement and the rising drama through them — well-structured synopses come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Is still developing a sense of structural intent. Advice to choose each formal decision because it serves the story''s theme or emotional journey — purposeful structure comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (5, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Feature concepts are still emerging. Advice to test each idea with attention to conflict, subplot, and theme to sustain a whole feature before developing it — long-form thinking grows through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Establishes a clear premise and central conflict, giving the short film a focused narrative direction.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Constructs a well-paced 20-minute script with precise beat structuring, strong scene progression, and confident control of narrative rhythm.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Offers critical, comparative analysis of a screenwriter''s work, clearly identifying differences in voice, structure, and thematic concerns.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Applies insights from screenwriter study to their own work, showing real awareness of voice, form, and narrative choices.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Expands a one-page idea into a detailed synopsis, with clear escalation of stakes and confident narrative layering.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Develops a feature treatment that sustains narrative progression, with coherent arcs and consistent tone.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Designs episodic structures with distinct episode arcs, sustaining continuity while advancing the overarching narrative.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'A', 'Constructs a comprehensive show bible that clearly presents concept, world, character grid, and season-level progression.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Understands premise well. Advice to define the central conflict in one sentence — who wants what, and what stands in the way — so the story focuses sharply, a clarity that comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Develops a structured short film script. Advice to refine pacing by checking that each scene advances the story and tightening transitions between them — smoother progression comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Engages with screenwriter study. Advice to compare two works directly on voice, structure, and theme and ask why each choice was made — deeper comparative analysis develops through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Shows awareness of authorial voice. Advice to identify the qualities admired in other writers and deliberately try them in your own scenes — a consistent personal voice comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Expands ideas into a synopsis. Advice to raise the stakes at each turning point and layer in subplot or theme for depth — strong escalation comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'The treatment conveys overall story direction. Advice to track each arc and hold a consistent tone scene to scene for a more cohesive whole — this consistency comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'Episodic structure is identifiable. Advice to give each episode its own self-contained arc and hook while still feeding the season story — distinct, varied episodes come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'B', 'The show bible communicates the core idea. Advice to expand the world with concrete rules and detail, and to map how the story grows across the season — a robust bible comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Has a basic understanding and grasp of premise. Advice to state the central idea in one clear line — who wants what, against what — so the whole narrative coheres around it, a focus that comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Is beginning to script short films. Advice to outline a clear beginning, middle, and end and check each scene moves the story forward — steady pacing and direction in the short form come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'The author study is mostly descriptive so far. Advice to compare two works side by side and ask why each creative choice was made — analytical, comparative insight grows through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Limited understanding of Authorial voice. Advice to name specific qualities admired in other writers and deliberately try them in your own scenes — a personal voice emerges through repeated and honest practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'The synopsis shows limited expansion of the original idea. Advice to expand it by deepening the world, clarifying character intentions, and raising dramatic tension at each turn — fuller development comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'The treatment is taking shape. Advice to track each character''s arc and build a clear emotional progression with a consistent tone across the story — a cohesive treatment comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'Episodic writing shows limited differntiation between episodes. Advice to give each episode its own arc, hook, and shape while still serving the season — distinct, varied episodes come through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'C', 'The show bible is incomplete. Advice to define the concept in one line, sketch each main character, and map the series direction so the bible reads as a complete, cohesive whole — this comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'The short film script requires clarity yet to shape. Advice to define the premise and central conflict, outline a clear structure, and aim each scene at the resolution — a purposeful short comes through repeated writing and film practice. You are in the final semester - so please work on this.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Author study needs deeper analytical engagement. Advice to practice comparing themes, structure, and approach across two works and explain the differences. Deeper analytical engagement is essential for a film graduate and calls for immersive film viewing and analytical practice.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Author study lacks analysis, with no meaningful comparison of works. Please develop a more analytical approach by exploring the purpose and impact of specific creative choices. When watching films immersre yourself and pay close attention to the Writing and Directorial choices.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Student is yet to discover a personal voice. Voice is important for writers. Advice to review your own scripts for recurring themes, rhythms, and choices, and to consider how they shape your writing — a clear authorial voice emerges through reflection of who is teing the story, repeated self practice as well as understanding how voice is expressed by other writers.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Student needs support to develop ideas into synopses. Advice to practice laying out the idea with a clear beginning, middle, and end as ordered beats and link them as cause and effect . Building a coherent synopsis required for a final semester student.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Episodic writing still developing and requires clearer arcs. Advice to give each episode its own arc, hold continuity between them, and plan how the season builds — long-form writing progression comes through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'Episode writing needs structure. Advice to give each episode a clear arc and track continuity across episodes, building up long-form writing step by step — this skill develops through repeated practice and feedback.'),
  (6, 'screenwriting', 'D', 'The show bible needs clearer articulation. Advice to practice stating the concept in one line, map the key character dynamics, and outline the series structure — a clear, well-designed bible comes through repeated practice and feedback. Please work on it.'),
  (1, 'cinematography', 'A', 'Demonstrates clear and confident control over exposure and colour, keeping shots consistent. To reach the next level, push subtle tonal choices to express mood.'),
  (1, 'cinematography', 'A', 'Applies lenses and depth of field purposefully to enhance visual storytelling. A strong foundation to build on as you explore more expressive focal choices.'),
