  (2, 'cinematography', 'B', 'Maintains a sense of rhythm and pacing. Advice to develop greater consistency by rehearsing tempo with the actors and editor in mind, so visual flow holds across the scene through regular practice.'),
  (2, 'cinematography', 'B', 'Plans camera movements with intent. Advice to align them more closely with narrative progression by mapping each move to a story beat in pre-production, sharpening through regular practice and review.'),
  (2, 'cinematography', 'B', 'Connects emotion with camera movement in parts. Advice to strengthen this by choosing move speed and direction that mirror the character’s state, a sensitivity built through regular practice.'),
