  (1, 'sound_design', 'A', 'Demonstrates high-level clarity in Human Auditory System. Continue observing the real world soundscapes on a daily basis. Good work.'),
  (1, 'sound_design', 'A', 'Demonstrates high-level clarity in Properties and Behaviour of Sound & Aural Perception vs Microphone Behaviour. Observe and analyse self-aural behaviour in everyday life. Keep it up.'),
  (1, 'sound_design', 'A', 'Demonstrates high-level clarity in Audio-Visual Relationships & Spatial and Temporal Relationships of Sound. Research into variations in familiar soundscapes through the days and seasons. Good work.'),
  (1, 'sound_design', 'A', 'Demonstrates high-level control and clarity in Portable Audio Recording Devices. Explore all the features available of the devices. Keep it up.'),
  (1, 'sound_design', 'A', 'Demonstrates high-level control and clarity in Location Sound Recording. Keep practising to achieve smoother consistent recordings. Good work.'),
  (1, 'sound_design', 'A', 'Demonstrates high-level clarity in Recording & Editing Ambiences. Work towards decoding the individual layers of the ambience recordings. Keep it up.'),
  (1, 'sound_design', 'A', 'Demonstrates high-level clarity in Editing & Mixing Sound Elements using Sound Editing Software. Work towards achieving better mixes for more narrative impact. Good work.'),
  (1, 'sound_design', 'A', 'Demonstrates high-level control and clarity in all the Semester I learning outcomes. Practice more with different raw materials across different genres. Keep it up.'),
  (1, 'sound_design', 'B', 'Shows a good understanding of Human Auditory System. Advice to develop this further: observe everyday soundscapes daily and study how the ear perceives sound — this listening foundation underpins everything a sound designer does. Regular practice will help strengthen this further.'),
  (1, 'sound_design', 'B', 'Shows a good understanding of Properties and Behaviour of Sound & Aural Perception vs Microphone Behaviour. Advice to develop this further: analyse how sound behaves around you and how it differs from what a microphone captures — this sharpens the critical listening the craft is built on. Regular practice will help strengthen this further.'),
  (1, 'sound_design', 'B', 'Shows a good understanding of Audio-Visual Relationships & Spatial and Temporal Relationships of Sound. Advice to develop this further: study how sound and picture interact across space and time in scenes you admire to build an instinct for what a moment should sound like. Regular practice will help strengthen this further.'),
  (1, 'sound_design', 'B', 'Shows a good understanding of Portable Audio Recording Devices. Advice to develop this further: practise with more recording sessions and explore every feature of the recorders to build the muscle memory for fast, reliable field work. Regular practice will help strengthen this further.'),
  (1, 'sound_design', 'B', 'Shows a good understanding of Location Sound Recording. Advice to develop this further: practise mic placement and monitor levels on headphones across more sessions to capture the clean, consistent location tracks professionals rely on. Regular practice will help strengthen this further.'),
  (1, 'sound_design', 'B', 'Shows a good understanding of Recording & Editing Ambiences. Advice to develop this further: go on more recording trips and learn to decode the individual layers of an ambience to build richer textures and cleaner recordings. Regular practice will help strengthen this further.'),
  (1, 'sound_design', 'B', 'Shows a good understanding of Editing & Mixing Sound Elements using Sound Editing Software. Advice to develop this further: practise regularly in the editing software and aim for cleaner, better-balanced mixes — this technical fluency is what gives a film narrative impact. Regular practice will help strengthen this further.'),
  (1, 'sound_design', 'B', 'Shows a solid grasp of all the Semester I learning outcomes. Advice to fine-tune each skill through regular practice projects across different genres — consistency and polish come through regular practice.'),
  (1, 'sound_design', 'C', 'Currently student remains at a basic level with Human Auditory System. Advice to build this up: observe everyday soundscapes daily and study how the ear perceives sound — this listening foundation underpins everything a sound designer does. Regular practice will help build steadier control and consistency.'),
  (1, 'sound_design', 'C', 'Currently student is at a basic level with Properties and Behaviour of Sound & Aural Perception vs Microphone Behaviour. Advice to build this up: analyse how sound behaves around you and how it differs from what a microphone captures — this sharpens the critical listening the craft is built on. Regular practice will help build steadier control and consistency.'),
