  (1, 'sound_design', 'D', 'Must attend classes regularly to achieve improvement in all the Semester learning outcomes. Advice to attend consistently and take part in every practical session, building the semester''s skills through steady, hands-on regular practice.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'A', 'Demonstrates high-level clarity in Attributes of Tonality, Pitch, and Amplitude in Dialogue Scenes. Start comparing between different characters, situations, & inter-persoanl relations through watching films and shows. Good work.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'A', 'Demonstrates high-level clarity in Characteristics and Applications of Different Microphones. Explore more by using them in different scenarios. Keep it up.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'A', 'Demonstrates high-level control and clarity in Different Audio Devices used in Sound Production. Experiment with different brands and models to understand differences in features and quality. Good work.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'A', 'Demonstrates high-level control and clarity in Sound Recording & Sound Editing of Dialogue Scenes. Research into advanced techniques utilized on professional film productions. Keep it up.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'A', 'Demonstrates high-level clarity in Workflow from Pre-Production to Post-Production of Sound in Film & TV Industry. Good work.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'A', 'Demonstrates high-level control and clarity in Making Sound Stories. Can experiment with different genres and research into the business side of the industry. Keep it up.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'A', 'Demonstrates high-level control and clarity in Sound Designing for Animation & VFX. Should work on practice projects and start building a demo showreel. Good work.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'A', 'Demonstrates high-level control and clarity in all the Semester II learning outcomes. Keep it up.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'B', 'Shows a good understanding of Attributes of Tonality, Pitch, and Amplitude in Dialogue Scenes. Advice to develop this further: watch dialogue scenes closely and compare tone, pitch and loudness across characters and situations to develop the ear needed to shape expressive dialogue. Regular practice will help strengthen this further.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'B', 'Shows a good understanding of Characteristics and Applications of Different Microphones. Advice to develop this further: run test recordings with different mics and compare the results to learn which microphone suits which situation. Regular practice will help strengthen this further.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'B', 'Shows a good understanding of Different Audio Devices used in Sound Production. Advice to develop this further: read the equipment manuals and try every feature of each device to build confident, fluent handling of the gear. Regular practice will help strengthen this further.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'B', 'Shows a good understanding of Sound Recording & Sound Editing of Dialogue Scenes. Advice to develop this further: take part in more practical recording exercises and analyse professional dialogue workflows to refine both recording and editing of dialogue. Regular practice will help strengthen this further.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'B', 'Shows a good understanding of Workflow from Pre-Production to Post-Production of Sound in Film & TV Industry. Advice to develop this further: trace the full sound workflow from pre-production to post on real projects to build a clear map of how each stage feeds the next. Regular practice will help strengthen this further.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'B', 'Shows a good understanding of Making Sound Stories. Advice to develop this further: build the story world through its soundscape and explore audiobooks and audio dramas across genres to develop strong sound-led storytelling. Regular practice will help strengthen this further.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'B', 'Shows a good understanding of Sound Designing for Animation & VFX. Advice to develop this further: work on more sample projects, layer effects and study behind-the-scenes breakdowns of animated films to build a designer’s toolkit and a showreel. Regular practice will help strengthen this further.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'B', 'Shows a solid grasp of all the Semester II learning outcomes. Advice to refine each skill through more practice projects and self-review of the results — consistency and polish come through regular practice.'),
