  (2, 'sound_design', 'C', 'Currently at a basic level with Sound Recording & Sound Editing of Dialogue Scenes. Advice to build this up: take part in more practical recording exercises and analyse professional dialogue workflows to refine both recording and editing of dialogue. Regular practice will help build steadier control and consistency.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'C', 'Currently at a basic level with Workflow from Pre-Production to Post-Production of Sound in Film & TV Industry. Advice to build this up: trace the full sound workflow from pre-production to post on real projects to build a clear map of how each stage feeds the next. Regular practice will help build steadier control and consistency.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'C', 'Currently at a basic level with Making Sound Stories. Advice to build this up: build the story world through its soundscape and explore audiobooks and audio dramas across genres to develop strong sound-led storytelling. Regular practice will help build steadier control and consistency.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'C', 'Currently at a basic level with Sound Designing for Animation & VFX. Advice to build this up: work on more sample projects, layer effects and study behind-the-scenes breakdowns of animated films to build a designer’s toolkit and a showreel. Regular practice will help build steadier control and consistency.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'C', 'Currently at a basic level across the Semester II learning outcomes. Advice to take a more proactive approach — practise each exercise regularly and seek feedback, as steady hands-on work is how these foundations are built. Regular practice will help build steadier control and consistency.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'D', 'Requires significant improvement in Attributes of Tonality, Pitch, and Amplitude in Dialogue Scenes. Advice to listen closely to the soundscapes of films and compare tone, pitch and loudness across characters and situations, developing the ear to shape expressive dialogue through regular practice.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'D', 'Requires significant improvement in Characteristics and Applications of Different Microphones. Advice to observe sound actively in films, shows and live events, and run test recordings with different mics to learn which microphone suits which situation through regular practice.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'D', 'Requires significant improvement in Different Audio Devices used in Sound Production. Advice to read the equipment manuals and try every feature of each device, building confident, fluent handling of the gear through regular practice.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'D', 'Requires significant improvement in Sound Recording & Sound Editing of Dialogue Scenes. Advice to take part in more practical recording exercises and analyse professional dialogue workflows, refining both recording and editing of dialogue through regular practice.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'D', 'Requires significant improvement in Workflow from Pre-Production to Post-Production of Sound in Film & TV Industry. Advice to trace the full sound workflow from pre-production to post through self-practice exercises and projects, building a clear map of how each stage feeds the next through regular practice.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'D', 'Requires significant improvement in Making Sound Stories. Advice to build the story world through its soundscape and explore audiobooks and audio dramas across genres, developing strong sound-led storytelling through regular practice.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'D', 'Requires significant improvement in Sound Designing for Animation & VFX. Advice to work on more sample projects, layer effects and study behind-the-scenes breakdowns, building a designer''s understanding and toolkit through regular practice.'),
  (2, 'sound_design', 'D', 'Requires significant improvement in all the Semester II learning outcomes. Advice to attend classes regularly and take part in exercises to grasp the fundamentals, developing a flair for sound through regular practice.'),
